AD_FIELD.HELP: A more descriptive identifier (that does need to be unique) of a record/document that is used as a default search option along with the search key (that is unique and mostly shorter). It is up to 60 characters in length.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Activity
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A distinct activity defined and used in activity based management.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Activities indicate tasks that are performed and used to utilize Activity based Costing

AD_FIELD.NAME: Storage Bin
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A set of coordinates (x, y, z) which help locate an item in a warehouse.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Locator ID indicates where in a Warehouse a product is located.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Accounting Schema for Income Statement
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Accounting Schema for Income Statement
AD_FIELD.HELP: Accounting Schema for Income Statement creation.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Project
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Identifier of a project defined within the Project & Service Management module.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Identifier of a project defined within the Project & Service Management module.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Movement Date
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The date that a certain item is moved from one location to another.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Movement Date indicates the date that a product moved in or out of inventory. This is the result of a shipment, receipt or inventory movement.

AD_FIELD.NAME: G/L Item
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An alias for the Account Combination which can be commonly used in daily operations.
AD_FIELD.HELP: General ledger item.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Movement Quantity
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The number of items being moved from one location to another.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Movement Quantity indicates the quantity of a product that has been moved.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Description
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A space to write additional related information.
AD_FIELD.HELP: A description is limited to 255 characters.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Flavour
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Flavour of a product, used as a dimension in reporting
AD_FIELD.HELP: Flavour of a product, used as a dimension in reporting

AD_FIELD.NAME: Actual Amount
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The actual amount
AD_FIELD.HELP: Actual amount indicates the agreed upon amount for a document.

AD_FIELD.NAME: List Price
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The official net price of a product in a specified currency.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Net List Price is the official price stated by the selected pricelist and the currency of the document.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Line Net Amount
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The final amount of a specified line, based only on quantities and prices.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Indicates the line net amount based on the quantity and the actual price. Any additional charges or freight are not included.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Print Details on Pick List
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Print detail BOM elements on the pick list
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Print Details on Pick List indicates that the BOM element products will print on the Pick List as opposed to this product.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Client
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Client for this installation.
AD_FIELD.HELP: A Client is a company or a legal entity. You cannot share data between Clients.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Life use
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Units of use until the asset is not usable anymore
AD_FIELD.HELP: Life use and the actual use may be used to calculate the depreciation

AD_FIELD.NAME: Starting Period
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: First period for the revenue plan.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Booking starts at last day of selected period and lasts for the selected number of periods.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Search Key
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A fast method for finding a particular record.
AD_FIELD.HELP:
A search key allows for a fast method of finding a particular record. If you leave the search key empty, the system automatically creates a numeric number originating from a document sequence defined in the "Document Sequence" window. The sequence naming convention follows a rule "DocumentNo_TableName", where TableName is the actual name of the database table (e.g. C_Order).
Usually, company's internal identifiers for various records (products, customers, etc) are stored here.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Description
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A space to write additional related information.
AD_FIELD.HELP: A description is limited to 255 characters.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Import Inventory
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Import Inventory
AD_FIELD.HELP: Import Inventory for opening balance

AD_FIELD.NAME: Currency
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: An accepted medium of monetary exchange that may vary across countries.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Indicates the currency to be used when processing this document.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Sequence Number
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The order of records in a specified document.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Sequence indicates the order of records

AD_FIELD.NAME: Active
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating whether this record is available for use or de-activated.
AD_FIELD.HELP: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reporting. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for auditing purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are existing invoices for it. By de-activating the Business Partner you prevent it from being used in future transactions.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Quantity
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The number of a certain item.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Quantity indicates the number of a specific product or item for this document.
